ca.ualberta.cmput301f14t16.easya.Model

Class Queue

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Thread
      • ca.ualberta.cmput301f14t16.easya.Model.Queue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable

    public class Queue
extends java.lang.Thread
    Creates a new Thread that automatically processes new Content created by the user. The Thread will store the newly received Content in a pending queue, and regularly check for a new connection. Once one is found, all items in the pending queue will be pushed, and the queue will be cleared. In practice, this will more or less immediately push any new Content when the device has an active Internet connection, and store any new Content until one is found if not.
    Author:
    Cauani
